Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 26/02/2025

Thank you for using Leaf! Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you interact with Leaf on GitHub.

1. Information We Collect

User Data: Leaf may collect limited user information such as GitHub usernames and interactions with the bot.

Logs: We may store logs of interactions for debugging and improving Leaf’s performance.

No Sensitive Data: We do not collect sensitive personal data such as passwords, financial details, or private repository contents.

2. How We Use Your Data

To provide and improve Leaf’s functionalities.

To analyze usage patterns for optimization.

To debug and fix issues.

3. Data Storage and Security

All data is stored securely and is not shared with third parties.

Logs are kept for a limited period and are deleted periodically.

We implement security measures to protect against unauthorized access.

4. Third-Party Services

Leaf may interact with third-party APIs (e.g., GitHub API), which have their own privacy policies.

We do not share your information with advertisers or other external services.

5. Your Rights

You can request the deletion of any data collected by Leaf.

You can stop using Leaf at any time to prevent further data collection.

6. Updates to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected on this page.

For any questions, contact us on Discord.
